Three methods for adding CSS

Inline,Internal,External

------------ Inline CSS ------------
	<html>
		<head>
				<h1 style="color:green">In-line CSS</h1>
		</head>
	</html>	

------------ Internal CSS ------------
-->> Style tags must be present in head tag
	<html>
	<head>
		<style>
			p
			{ 
			 color:#009;
			 font-size:18px;
			 font-weight:700;
			}
			h2
			{
				background-color: pink;
				color: red;
			}
		</style>
			<h1>In-line CSS</h1>
			<h2> This is h2 tag text </h2>
	</head>
	<body>
		<p>
			Paragraph1
		</p>
		<p>
			Paragraph 2
		</p>

	
	</body>
</html>

------------ External CSS ------------
To Target selectors
h1
{
	
}
p
{
	
}
class -> .


padding shorthand

p
{
	margin: top right bottom left;
	margin: 5px 10px 5px 10px
}